Two stars for the memories. I've had many enjoyable meals at the Farm with a few mishaps over time as one would expect. This is my most recent experience a few days ago. I dropped by a few days ago for lunch to celebrate finished Â taxes and an expected refund. I ordered a medium rare burger with salad instead of fries. Burger #1 was raw in the middle, so I sent it back to the kitchen. Burger #2 was also raw in the middle with the meat blood visible through the cheese on top. I sent burger # 2 back to the kitchen, just as I had burger #1. Finally, 45 minutes after ordering, Burger #3 was hot, cooked and edible. My advice: look "inside" before you eat it. M
